title: Sidewall, "Colinette", 1920–50
creditline: Gift of The Museum at The Fashion Institute of Technology
description: Two putti figures holding cameo with bust, standing on delicate scrolls, with suspended cartouche. The cartouche contains a scene of a seated female with animal nursing baby animal, and 2 putti, one holding a bird on tether. Printed in brown, yellow ocher and white on tan ground. Printed in selvedge: "Made in France".

tombstone.epitaph:
Sidewall, "Colinette", 1920–50.
1920–50. Block-printed on continuous paper. Gift of The Museum at The Fashion Institute of Technology. 1998-75-109.
